title: Snow squall warning issued for parts of the region | CTV Barrie News
text:
A blustery and snowy night is in store for parts of Simcoe County and Grey County.
Environment Canada says snow squalls and 60 km/h winds could develop Thursday night and continue into Friday morning.
This system could bring localized snowfall amounts of 15 centimetres. Due to the high winds, Environment Canada says conditions will vary.
A snow squall warning is in effect for:
Barrie - Collingwood - Hillsdale Midland - Coldwater - Orr Lake Orillia - Lagoon City - Washago Owen Sound - Blue Mountains - Northern Grey County Hanover - Dundalk - Southern Grey County A snow squall watch has been issued for:
Innisfil - New Tecumseth - Angus Newmarket - Georgina - Northern York Region Uxbridge - Beaverton - Northern Durham Region The weather office says more snow is expected to begin falling on Friday afternoon, as an Alberta clipper approaches.
